HEADWORD: Cranium
<hw>Cra"ni*um</hw> <pr>(kr?"n?-?m)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> E. <plw>Craniums</plw> (-<?/mz), L. <plw>Crania</plw>
<pr>(-<?/)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <?/<?/<?/<?/; akin to
<grk>ka`ra</grk> head.]</ety> <def>The skull of an animal; especially,
that part of the skull, either cartilaginous or bony, which immediately
incloses the brain; the brain case or brainpan. See
<er>Skull</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

